<HEADLINE>
FT  24 NOV 94 / UK Company News: L&amp;G trust launch will raise minimum Pounds
29.8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Legal &amp; General Group is inviting offers for up to 150m shares at 100p each,
with warrants attached on a 1-for-5 basis, in its new investment trust, the
Legal &amp; General Recovery Investment Trust.
The minimum investment is Pounds 1,000 with management charges of  3/4 per
cent.
Panmure Gordon, sponsor to the offer, has received irrevocable undertakings
for up to 41.3m shares. With 31.2m shares having been underwritten the offer
will raise, net of expenses, a minimum Pounds 29.8m and a maximum Pounds
143.4m.
The warrants can be exercised for 100p within 10 years. The trust has a life
of not more than 10 years.
The aim of the trust is to achieve long-term capital growth and outperform
the FT-SE-A All-Share Index by investing in UK-quoted equities with recovery
potential.
It is being managed by the same team as the Legal &amp; General UK Recovery Unit
Trust.
