<HEADLINE>
FT  24 NOV 94 / Observer: Sheepish
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pfizer, the US drugs company, has just paid Dollars 1.45bn for SmithKline
Beecham's animal health business which includes a thriving sideline in
'swine and companion animal vaccines'.
Come, come, Pfizer. If you are going to call a pet a 'companion animal',
surely a swine should be an ungulate omnivorous mammal. Even swine have
feelings.
