<HEADLINE>
FT  24 NOV 94 / Letters to the Editor: Cheers for a tight quango
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr T W R WHITE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Re your article, 'Labour attacks ministers over spending on wine'
(November 21), is Mr Alan Milburn, the Labour MP, a teetotaller?
I am sure the Labour party serves wine at its official gatherings and I
would have thought Sir Ewen Fergusson, head of the government hospitality
fund advisory committee for the purchase of wine, should be congratulated
for providing wine at an average of Pounds 5.26 a bottle. He also seems to
run a tight quango if it only costs Pounds 1,500 a year to run.
T W R White,
