<HEADLINE>
FT  24 NOV 94 / Curry dashes hopes to increase private rented accommodation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBYN CHALMERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr David Curry, the housing minister, yesterday dashed hopes that a class of
investment trust to increase private rented accommodation would be
introduced in the Budget, Robyn Chalmers writes.
The trusts aim to boost institutional investment in the private rented
sector. They would be free from capital gains tax and pay corporation tax at
the lower rate of 25 per cent.
Mr Curry said that no industry estimates had been provided on levels of
subsidy needed.
Once an estimate had been concluded he would be prepared to explore the
option in line with the government's stated aim of encouraging growth in the
sector.
</TEXT>
