FT  24 NOV 94 / Mexico's deputy attorney general resigns
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TED BARDACKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Mario Ruiz Massieu yesterday resigned as Mexico's deputy attorney general
after accusing leaders of the ruling Institutional Revolutionary party of a
cover-up in investigating the murder of his brother Francisco, writes Ted
Bardacke in Mexico City. The IPC stock market immediately fell 3.3 per cent
before recovering to close 1.4 per cent down.
Mr Ruiz Massieu also quit as lead investigator in the murder of his brother,
the PRI's secretary general. Mr Massieu claimed he had proof Mr Humberto
Benitez, attorney general, Mr Ignacio Pichardo, PRI president, and Ms Maria
de los Angeles Moreno, ex-majority leader in Congress, had conspired to
cover up participation of PRI members.
