<HEADLINE>
FT  24 NOV 94 / Tourists urged to quit Gambia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SKAPINKER, Leisure Industries Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The British Foreign Office yesterday called in tour operators yesterday and
advised them to bring more than 2,000 holidaymakers home from Gambia because
of a deterioration in the political situation. However, Gambia Experience,
one of the largest operators to the country, said it would allow its
customers to decide whether or not they wanted to continue their holidays.
The Foreign Office said it had been monitoring the situation in Gambia since
a coup, in which Lt Yahya Jammet seized power from Sir Dawda Jawara, and
there had been a steady deterioration. It said the political situation was
uncertain and could deteriorate quickly. The advisory notice follows an
attempted counter coup against on November 11 which Lieutenant Jammet blamed
on former finance minister Mr Bakary Dabo.
</TEXT>
