<HEADLINE>
FT  23 NOV 94 / London Stock Exchange: Strong debut for TeleWest
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and JEFFREY BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cable television operator TeleWest made a storming stock market debut,
closing 3 1/2 ahead of the 182p flotation price in levels of activity that
came close to heart stopping for an offering of just 216m shares.
Turnover of 59m was nearly six times the level of volume in BTR, the most
actively traded Footsie stock. Kleinwort Benson Securities, joint broker to
the issue, was said to be responsible for around half of yesterday's trade.
The driving force behind the bumper trading was thought to be interaction
between the London and New York tranches of the issue, plus a certain amount
of switching with BT, which fell 9 to 379p.
