<HEADLINE>
FT  23 NOV 94 / International Company News: Wesfarmers, MRI in venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Wesfarmers, the Australian diversified rural services and resources group,
said yesterday it had entered a joint venture with Medical Research
International to look at coal-related projects in China, writes Nikki Tait.
MRI is a vehicle for Mr Oei Hong Leong, the Hong Kong-based entrepreneur. It
recently announced that it would head a consortium to build a ADollars 1.2bn
(USDollars 90m) coal slurry pipeline in China.
Wesfarmers and MRI said they had last month met Mr Wang Shenghao, China's
minister for coal, to 'explore opportunities for co-operative coal-mining
ventures in China'.
