<HEADLINE>
FT  23 NOV 94 / International Company News: Communications investment fund
to be launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Montgomery Asset Management, the San Francisco-based investment manager, and
Barings Securities, part of the UK investment banking group, yesterday
announced a Dollars 100m investment fund which will focus on communications
and services in the emerging markets. The Montgomery Emerging Communications
Fund will place up to 10m shares.
Mr Oscar Castro, who currently manages the Montgomery Global Communications
Fund, will act as principal portfolio manager for the fund, which will be
registered as a closed end investment company in Bermuda.
Baring Brothers is sponsor to the issue and Baring Securities is the placing
agent. The placing is not underwritten.
'New technologies can offer emerging markets countries cheaper and faster
solutions to their communications needs,' said Barings. 'For example, in
some parts of Thailand and the Philippines, cellular telephone networks are
being installed instead of standard land lines.'
Montgomery will also target opportunities in broadcasting, media and cable
TV.
</TEXT>
