<HEADLINE>
FT  23 NOV 94 / International Company News: Cost-cutting sustains recovery
at OMV
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
OMV, the Austrian integrated petroleum and chemicals group, reported a
Sch123m (Dollars 11.2m) pre-tax profit in the third quarter, as its recovery
from two years of losses continued, driven mainly by cost-cutting. The
company recorded losses of Sch190m for the same period last year.
Sales at the partially-privatised group rose 8.6 per cent to Sch21.07bn,
reflecting 'slightly improved' overall market conditions. However, the
exploration and production sector remained in loss due to low crude oil
prices and a weak dollar.
The directors said they remained confident the group would achieve a profit
in the full year.
The gas division was once again the largest contributor to earnings, with
third-quarter pre-tax profit almost unchanged at Sch320m. Turnover was up 10
per cent to Sch1.74bn.
The refining division saw its lowest margins since 1989, with sales down 1.5
per cent to Sch11.7bn, mainly because of lower prices for oil products. The
division posted profit of Sch70m profit, 12.5 per cent lower than in the
third quarter of 1993.
Profit in the marketing division was down nearly 20 per cent to Sch130m.
</TEXT>
